    "created_at": "2016-01-04T09:38:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-05T07:06:26Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz @omrilitov Any updates on this? I am actually in the need of this feature. Thanks!\n\n**[ Edit ]** It seems to me that using an (unsigned) integer big enough to hold a pointer (even on a 64bit machine) would suffice, as the relevant type `AcceleratedWidget` is already defined as either a pointer (`OS_WIN`, `OS_IOS`, `OS_MACOSX`, `OS_ANDROID`) or an integer (`USE_X11`, `USE_OZONE`).\n\nI understand that this may not hold true for any and all native handles you might expose at a later stage (although I can't come up with an actual example), and see how making such handles uniformly be stored as `Buffer`s would help standardize them and make them future proof, but I would still like your opinion on this.\n"
  },
